# audio-mcp local signing + notarization credentials
# ---------------------------------------------------
# Copy this file to `.env.signing` and fill in your values.
# `.env.signing` is gitignored and must never be committed.
#
# Signing is OPTIONAL: if these variables are unset (or `.env.signing`
# is missing), `scripts/build-helper.sh` produces an unsigned binary.
# That path is used by contributors who don't have an Apple Developer
# account. Official releases should always be signed + notarized.

# --- Code signing (Developer ID Application cert in Keychain) ---
# Matches the exact identity string shown by:
#   security find-identity -v -p codesigning | grep "Developer ID Application"
# e.g. "Developer ID Application: Your Name (APYL42WZVK)"
APPLE_SIGNING_IDENTITY=""

# --- Notarization (App Store Connect API key) ---
# 10-char team identifier from developer.apple.com → Membership
APPLE_TEAM_ID=""

# UUID from appstoreconnect.apple.com → Users and Access → Integrations
# (shown at the top of the API keys panel)
APPLE_ISSUER_ID=""

# 10-char key ID, baked into the downloaded .p8 filename
# (e.g. AuthKey_KT43R53VC3.p8 → key id is KT43R53VC3)
APPLE_KEY_ID=""

# Absolute path to the .p8 private key file. Keep this outside the repo.
APPLE_KEY_PATH=""
